    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix heap buffer overflow in nr_rrc_ue_decode_ccch and related functions\n\n### Summary\nASN.1 decoding functions in the RRC layer used incorrect error handling that could lead to heap buffer overflow. The error checking condition only failed when there was a decode error AND no bytes were consumed. If a partial decode occurred, the function would continue with invalid data.\n\nThis fix changes the error checking to fail on any decode error.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_UE.c`: Updated error handling in ASN.1 decode functions to properly check for decode errors\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_UE.c`: Fixed nr_rrc_ue_decode_ccch and related functions to prevent buffer overflows\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_UE.c`: Changed error condition from `((dec_rval.code != RC_OK) && (dec_rval.consumed == 0))` to `(dec_rval.code != RC_OK)`\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Run OAI UE with fuzzed RRC messages\n2. Observe heap buffer overflow when ASN.1 decoder partially consumes invalid data\n3. Access to uninitialized structure members causes segfault or memory corruption\n\n"
}